    <briefdescription>
<para><bold> Auxiliary data structure for handling set of data blocks and includes usual MPI processes on them.</bold> </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Purpose</title><para></para>
</simplesect>
Auxiliary data structure for handling of data blocks (total number is n_) , which are stored in contiguous form in member data_ and includes usual MPI routines. The class identity is marked by <computeroutput>tid_</computeroutput> <formula id="18">$ \in $</formula> <computeroutput>(0,...,ntasks_-1)</computeroutput> and the value of the tid_ is just the MPI rank or 0 if MPI is not defined. Each data block j is owned by precisely one process, which is given by <computeroutput><ref refid="classcntr_1_1distributed__array_a52c8d4f0b99718b17eb77006c9b90956_1a52c8d4f0b99718b17eb77006c9b90956" kindref="member">tid</ref></computeroutput> <computeroutput>_map(j) = tid_</computeroutput>. The member maxlen marks the maximum size reserved for the block. NOTE: even if the block is not owned by the process, the space for the data is allocated; the ownership plays a role when the data are manipulated </para>
    </detaileddescription>
